<subSubSection lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="242" pageId="40" pageNumber="241" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,1412,2015]" lastBlockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="242" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1772,1799]" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[383,467,1772,1799]" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">MALE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[486,572,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–20. Phytomia spp., habitus, lateral view. 11. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 12. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 13. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 14. P. fucoides Bezzi ♂ 15. P. fusca Hull ♀ 16. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 17. P. varians Curran ♂ 18. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 19. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ 20 (copyright NRMS). P. fronto (Loew) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909051/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,658,1772,1799]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[677,765,1773,1800]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[281,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[271,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Figs 21–26. Phytomia spp., head, dorsal view. 21. P. bullata (Loew) ♀ 22. P. aurigera Bezzi ♀ 23. P. serena (Curran) ♀ 24. P. fusca Hull ♀ 25. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 27. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ Figs 27–28. Phytomia spp., head, lateral view. 27. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♀ 28. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909053/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="241">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Eye bare; holoptic, touching for distance slightly longer than length of ocellar triangle, facets subequal, only moderately enlarged in dorsal half. Frons brown to black; with greyish brown pollinosity, along eye margin more brownish; dispersed pilosity of short to medium long pale pile interspersed with few dark pile; rugose area shining brown, occupying about one-third of entire width and at about half of height of frons; with shorter dispersed pale pile. Face ground colour black; mainly weakly shining with sparse greyish brown pollinosity, below antennae more densely greyish pollinose; pilosity of short pale pile; strongly concave with facial tubercle rounded, strongly pronounced. Gena black, brownish pollinose narrowly along eye margin; with long pale pilosity. Occiput dorsal third black, with greyish pollinosity; ventrally more silvery to brown, with dispersed pale pile. Antennal segments black to black-brown; arista yellow-brown, in basal half with short pile equal to about one-third of pedicel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,261,287]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Thorax</emphasis>
. Scutum ground colour black; with dispersed greyish brown to brown pollinosity; covered with dense pile of short pale brownish pile interspersed with few darker pile, along lateral margin more whitish pile. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[210,291,333,360]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–36" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[242,1360,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[227,1360,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 29–36. Figs 29–34. Phytomia spp., hind leg, anterior view. 29. P. bullata (Loew) ♂ 30. P. serena (Curran) ♀ 31. P. bulligera (Austen) ♂ 32. P. austeni sp. nov. ♂ 33. P. bezzii Curran ♂ 34. P. memnon sp. nov. ♂ Figs 35–36: Phytomia spp., scutellum, dorsal view. 35. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 36. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909055" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909055/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) as scutum except more orange-brown, at least along posterior margin. Pleural sclerites ground colour black, with greyish pollinosity. Covered (except meron, anterior part of katepisternum, and anterior anepisternum) with long whitish or pale yellowish pile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,441,467]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Legs</emphasis>
. Black-brown to orange-brown, tarsal segments more orange. Fore leg, femur with short pale pilosity, anteriorly and posteriorly longer, and mixed with darker pile to variable extent, rarely predominantly black; tibia pale in basal half, apically black-brown, with short pale pilosity except in apical darker part where black pile. Mid leg, as fore leg except pilosity on femur and tibia entirely pale. Hind leg, femur more orange-brown; medium long pale pilosity except ventrally in apical fourth to fifth where black; tibia with basal third pale dorsally, otherwise orangebrown to dark brown; black pilosity except dorsally in basal part where pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,656,683]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Wing</emphasis>
. Largely hyaline (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[530,623,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Phytomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melas">
<emphasis box="[530,623,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">P. melas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[638,666,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[672,755,656,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–60" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,203,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[157,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 49–60. Phytomia spp., right wing. 49. P. pubipennis Bezzi ♀ 50. P. natalensis (Macquart) ♂ 51. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 52. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 53. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 54. P. fucoides Bezzi ♂ 55. P. fusca Hull ♀ 56. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 57. P. varians Curran ♂ 58. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 59. P. melas (Bezzi) ♀ 60. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909059/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), no microtrichia. At most fumose along anterior margin and surrounding venation. Calypters yellow brown; with fringe of pale pile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,728,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[332,465,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–84" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[182,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[156,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 73–84. Phytomia spp., abdomen, dorsal view. 73. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 74. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 75. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 76. P. fucoides Bezzi ♀ 77. P. fusca Hull ♀ 78. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 79. P. varians Curran ♀ 80. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 81- 82. P. melas (Bezzi) ♀; 83. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ 84. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909063/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Figs 83–84</figureCitation>
). Mainly black-brown, tergum 2 yellow-brown to orange-brown along anterior threefourths except for isolated brown rectangular transverse macula in medial part; tergum 3 yellow-brown to orangebrown along anterior margin for at most one-fourth of entire depth, sometimes interrupted medially; tergum 4 weakly shining black-brown, sometimes with narrow orange-brown fascia along anterior margin. Terga covered with dispersed short pale pile except posterior part of tergum 4 where some darker pile, along lateral margins with longer pale pilosity. No bullae. Sterna brown to black-brown; with widely dispersed long pale pile. Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[210,307,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–100" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,381,1702]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 85–100. Phytomia spp., male terminalia, dorsal view. 85. P. bullata (Loew). 86. P. aurigera Bezzi. 87. P. kroeberi (Bezzi). 88. P. bulligera (Austen). 89. P. austeni sp. nov. 90. P. bezzii Curran. 91. P. memnon sp. nov. 92. P. pubipennis Bezzi. 93. P. natalensis (Macquart). 94. P. curta (Loew). 95. P. pallida sp. nov. 96. P. erratica (Bezzi). 97. P. fucoides Bezzi. 98. P. incisa (Wiedemann). 99. P. melas (Bezzi). 100. P. poensis (Bezzi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909065/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,980,1007]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">FEMALE</emphasis>
. As male except for the following character states. Eye, facets of equal size (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1302,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[281,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[271,1316,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 21–28. Figs 21–26. Phytomia spp., head, dorsal view. 21. P. bullata (Loew) ♀ 22. P. aurigera Bezzi ♀ 23. P. serena (Curran) ♀ 24. P. fusca Hull ♀ 25. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 27. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♂ Figs 27–28. Phytomia spp., head, lateral view. 27. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♀ 28. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909053/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); dichoptic. Frons black ground colour; with greyish brown pollinosity, except in dorsal third where dark brown; covered with short intermixed pale and dark pile, in dorsal part more dark pile; rugose area shining brown to yellow-brown, occupying less than one-third width and equal in height to at most twice the ocellar triangle. Face with orange-brown patches. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[326,410,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–60" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,203,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[157,1431,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 49–60. Phytomia spp., right wing. 49. P. pubipennis Bezzi ♀ 50. P. natalensis (Macquart) ♂ 51. P. curta (Loew) ♂ 52. P. pallida sp. nov. ♂ 53. P. erratica (Bezzi) ♂ 54. P. fucoides Bezzi ♂ 55. P. fusca Hull ♀ 56. P. incisa (Wiedemann) ♂ 57. P. varians Curran ♂ 58. P. melas (Bezzi) ♂ 59. P. melas (Bezzi) ♀ 60. P. poensis (Bezzi) ♀" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909059/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
), fumose area sometimes more extensive. Extension and coloration of orange-brown markings variable, sometimes terga 2 and 3 completely black-brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
